      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Losing those closest to you can be incredibly isolating and devastating. The feeling of being a ghost in your own life, watching the world move on without you, can be suffocating. It's heartbreaking that the perceived realities of your life are slowly disappearing, leaving you with only the burden of existence. Recognize that this is a heavy emotional weight to carry, but you are still here, still experiencing emotions, and still deserving of connection and support.",
      "source": "target",
